    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02580.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>JOHN H. JOHNSTON.</name>
                    <name type="place">ALBERT EDW. JOHNSTON.</name>
                    <name type="place">J.H. JOHNSTON &#38; CO.,</name>
                    <name type="place">DIAMOND MERCHANTS AND JEWELERS,</name>
                    <name type="place">17 UNION SQUARE,</name>
                    <name type="place">CORNER BROADWAY &#38; 15TH STREET.</name>
                    <name type="place"><milestone unit="undeclared" rend="horbar-short-center"/></name>
                    <name type="place">ESTABLISHED 1844.</name>
                    <name type="place"><hi rend="italic">All Communications should be addressed to the firm.</hi></name>
                    <name type="place"><milestone unit="undeclared" rend="horbar-short-center"/></name>
                    <name type="place">TELEPHONE CALL: "916 - 18TH STREET."</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>305 E 14 St.</name>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>New York,<ptr target="loc.02580_n1"/> <handShift rend="manuscript"/><date when="1891-11-30">Nov 30 <handShift rend="printed"/>189<handShift rend="manuscript"/>1</date></name>
                    </dateline> 
                <salute>Dear Walt:</salute>
            </opener> 
                <p>Last Saturday night I was at the Dinner given by the Lotus
                    Club to Mons. Giacosa<ptr target="loc.02580_n2"/>&#8212;the Shakspear of Italy&#8212;whose Play on Wed. night at the Standard
                    Theater Sarah <choice><sic>Bernhard</sic><corr>Bernhardt</corr></choice><ptr target="loc.02580_n3"/> is to celebrate&#8212;
                </p> 
                <p> 
                    During the evening I had a good long half hour's talk with Bronson Howard<ptr target="n4257"/>
                    and he surprised me by telling me how much he thought of &#38; read L of G and said he wished
                    he had a good copy easy to hold and handle&#8212;and I recommended the 2 vol edition &#38; he
                    thanked me for offering
                    <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02580.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                    to write you for them&#8212;
                </p> 
                <p>
                    If you will send them to
                <address>
                    <addrLine>Bronson Howard</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>New Rochelle</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>N.Y.</addrLine>
                </address></p>
            <p>I will guarantee cash payment.</p>                     
                <p>4 weeks housed up&#8212;Up and at it now, but tire out easy, but am better every day&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Ever yours</salute>
                <signed>JHJ</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.02580.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.02580.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
